@startuml
' IOD(8)_Pj2_T-1 — User Story 8: Export Class Schedule
' Author: MayfairMI6

skinparam DefaultFontName Arial
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #444444
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam NoteBorderColor #AAAAAA

title IOD(8)_Pj2_T-1\nUS8: Export Class Schedule

note right: Author: MayfairMI6

start

:Prerequisite: schedule data has been imported\n(see US1 — Upload Excel File);

:Actor navigates to the Search & Filter Classes Page\n(or directly to the Export / Download Page);

if (Actor wants to filter before export?) then (yes)

  :Actor enters search criteria;

  #ADD8E6:**ref** UC_SEARCH — Search and Filter Classes
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  System retrieves matching classes from the database;

  :System displays filtered class list;

else (no)
  :Actor proceeds with full dataset;
endif

:Actor selects export format (Excel or CSV);
:Actor clicks "Download" / "Export";

#ADD8E6:**ref** UC_EXPORT — Export Schedule
────────────────────────────────────────────
System serializes the selected class data\ninto the chosen file format (xlsx or csv);

:System triggers file download in the browser;

:Actor receives downloaded schedule file\nfor distribution to departments and staff;

stop
@enduml
